Scenario
Silvio Peroni thinks that the class TallPerson is vague since there is no way to define a crisp height threshold that may separate tall from non-tall people.

Panos Alexopoulos, on the other hand, considers someone as tall when his/her height is at least 190cm. Thus, for Panos, the class TallPerson is not vague.

@prefix : <http://www.essepuntato.it/2013/10/vagueness/abox/>.
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>.
@prefix oa: <http://www.w3.org/ns/oa#>.
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>.
@prefix prov: <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#>.
@prefix vag: <http://www.essepuntato.it/2013/10/vagueness/>.
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>.
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>.

:TallPerson a owl:Class.

:silvio-peroni a :prov:Agent.

:silvio-vagueness-annotation-for-tall-person a vag:VaguenessAnnotation;
	oa:hasBody :silvio-vagueness-description-for-tall-person;
	oa:hasTarget :TallPerson;
	prov:wasAttributedTo :silvio-peroni.

:silvio-vagueness-description-for-tall-person a vag:DescriptionOfVagueness;
	vag:hasJustification :silvio-justification-for-vagueness-of-tall-person.

:silvio-justification-for-vagueness-of-tall-person a vag:Justification;
	vag:hasNaturalLanguageText 
		`Tall Person is vague because it's not possible to define the height threshold 
		between tall and non-tall.`.

:panos-alexopoulos a :prov:Agent.

:panos-vagueness-annotation-for-tall-person a vag:VaguenessAnnotation;
	oa:hasBody :panos-non-vagueness-description-for-tall-person;
	oa:hasTarget :TallPerson;
	prov:wasAttributedTo :panos-alexopoulos.

:panos-non-vagueness-description-for-tall-person a vag:DescriptionOfNonVagueness;
	vag:hasJustification :panos-justification-for-non-vagueness-of-tall-person.

:panos-justification-for-non-vagueness-of-tall-person a vag:Justification;
	vag:hasNaturalLanguageText `Tall Person is not vague because all the threshold is 190cm.`.

